channel.title: [317] Is my compiler stupid...? please read and help. [Deltascape source]
channel.description:
Ok guys... heres the deal, i have a deltascape source, and when i compile, i get this code: [code]client.java:450: ';' expected server.npcHandler.spawnANPC(2741, 2381, 5106, heightLevel) ^ 1 error Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
But heres whats in my client.java...
[code]server.npcHandler.spawnANPC(2741, 2381, 5106, heightLevel);[/code]
now notice after the parenthesis there is a semi-colen, but my compiler says there needs to be one there, please help guys...
